!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

unfold /ʌnˈfəʊld/

(unfolding,unfolded,unfolds) 

1. V-I If a situation unfolds , it develops and becomes known or understood. 逐渐明朗 

例： The outcome depends on conditions as well as how events unfold. 结果取决于条件以及事件如何发展。 

2. V-T/V-I If a story unfolds or if someone unfolds it, it is told to someone else. 使 (事情等) 传开; 传开 

例： Don's story unfolded as the cruise got under way. 唐的故事随着航游的开始而漫漫展开了。 

3. V-T/V-I If someone unfolds something which has been folded or if it unfolds , it is opened out and becomes flat. 展开 

例： He quickly unfolded the blankets and spread them on the mattress. 他迅速摊开毯子，铺在褥垫上。

</div>

